org.jcvi.jillion.core.residue

Interface ResidueSequence<R extends Residue,T extends ResidueSequence<R,T,B>,B extends ResidueSequenceBuilder<R,T>>

  • Type Parameters:
    R - the Type of Residue in this Sequence.
    T - the ResidueSequence implementation, needed for some of the return types to make sure it returns "this" type.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Iterable<R>, Sequence<R>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    NucleotideSequence, ProteinSequence, ReferenceMappedNucleotideSequence
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractResidueSequence

    public interface ResidueSequence<R extends Residue,T extends ResidueSequence<R,T,B>,B extends ResidueSequenceBuilder<R,T>>
extends Sequence<R>
    ResidueSequence is a Sequence of Residue that may contain gaps. There are extra methods to get the gap locations and convert from gap offsets to ungapped offsets and vice versa.
    Author:
    dkatzel

    • Method Detail

      • getGapOffsets

        List<Integer> getGapOffsets()
        Get a List of all the offsets into this sequence which are gaps. This list SHOULD be sorted by offset in ascending order. The size of the returned list should be the same as the value returned by getNumberOfGaps().
        Returns:
        a List of gap offsets as Integers.

      • getNumberOfGaps

        Returns:

      • getUngappedOffsetFor

        int getUngappedOffsetFor(int gappedOffset)
        Get the corresponding ungapped offset into this sequence for the given gapped offset.
        Parameters:
        gappedOffset - the offset into the gapped coordinate system of the desired nucleotide. This value must be a non-negative value that is less than the sequence length.
        Returns:
        the corresponding offset for the equivalent location in the ungapped sequence.
        Throws:
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - if the gappedOffset is negative or beyond the sequence length.

      • getGappedOffsetFor

        int getGappedOffsetFor(int ungappedOffset)
        Get the corresponding gapped offset into this sequence for the given ungapped offset. For example calling this method passing in a value of 0 will return the number of leading gaps in this sequence.
        Parameters:
        ungappedOffset - the offset into the ungapped coordinate system of the desired nucleotide. This value must be a non-negative value that is less than the sequence ungapped length.
        Returns:
        the corresponding offset for the equivalent location in the gapped sequence.
        Throws:
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - if the ungappedOffset is negative or if the computed gapped offset would extend beyond the sequence length.

      • kmers

        default Stream<Kmer<T>> kmers(int k)
        Create a new Stream of Kmers for all the k-mers of this entire sequence of the given kmer size.
        Parameters:
        k - the size of each kmer. For example a 3-mer would have k=3.
        Returns:
        a new Stream of Kmers which will never be null but may be empty if the sequence length is less than k.

        See Also:

      • kmers

        default Stream<Kmer<T>> kmers(int k,
                              Range range)
        Create a new Stream of Kmers for all the k-mers in the specified sub range of this sequence of the given kmer size.
        Parameters:
        k - the size of each kmer. For example a 3-mer would have k=3.
        range - the sub range to use; can not be null or out of range of the sequence.
        Returns:
        a new Stream of Kmers which will never be null but may be empty if the subrange sequence length is less than k.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if k is less than 1.
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - if Range contains values outside of the possible sequence offsets.
        Since:
        5.3
